name: Fat Fish

reviews.review_text:
Everything is good. I feel it is a bit costly for my pocket. May find some other better options at the same price.

On top of that you need to wait for 30 minutes to get a tablet.

Food taste was really good.

At least you can try this once whenever you are in Calangute.

Huge parking space.

Ambience is also okay.

Amazing food quality loved the dishes and all the local delights. This place offers a great ambience to chill out with friends and families. Great vibes to hang out. Usually, this place gets crowded and recommended to arrive earlier.

Great food and beer choices, fish dishes highly recommend. It's definitely worth the visit and great value for money..

Would love to be back again to try more other dishes.

Wait staff need better training. They were holding glasses from the inside surface of the glass with no tray. Also, they only offer mineral water which is twice as expensive as outside and when I asked for regular water the waiter staff said it was from the tap and made a face like as if it was radioactively contaminated or something.

Food: Crab soup - lacked salt and was a simple crab broth with a few pieces of crab.
Prawn Butter garlic- not great not too bad. Would probably skip this dish the next time.
Seafood pizza - star of the show honestly. Was far better than the seafood pizza I’ve had at Artichoke’s New York too. The seafood pizza is a must try.

description:
### Restaurant Review: Fat Fish, Arpora

Nestled in the vibrant locale of Arpora, *Fat Fish* boasts an impressive rating of **4.1 out of 5**, cultivated from over **30,821 reviews**. A frequent choice among seafood aficionados, the restaurant showcases a menu rich with **crab**, **king fish**, and the ever-popular **fish thali**, making it a robust contender in the local dining scene.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering *Fat Fish*, guests are greeted by a welcoming ambiance that strikes a balance between casual dining and cozy elegance. The décor, captured in various customer photos, hints at marine influences—think subtle blues and inviting wooden accents that echo the restaurant's seafood focus. Pictures highlight large windows that let in generous natural light, creating a warm and relaxed atmosphere. On busier days, the place can get crowded, so arriving early is advisable if you prefer a quieter dining experience. The overall vibe is further enhanced by soft, soothing music, providing the perfect backdrop for a meal with friends or family.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

What truly sets *Fat Fish* apart is its dedication to fresh, local ingredients, prominently featured in their standout dishes. The crab soup is a customer favorite, though some reviews suggest it could benefit from a touch more seasoning. Meanwhile, the prawn butter garlic, while a decent accompaniment, doesn’t quite steal the show. The real star of the menu, however, is undeniably the **seafood pizza**—a dish that has been touted as the highlight of the meal, rivaling even those from famed establishments in New York. 

With notable offerings of **king fish** and variations of **fish thalis**, diners can look forward to a sumptuous array of flavors and presentations. The photography shared by patrons captures beautifully plated dishes, showcasing the restaurant's focus on presentation and quality.

For those with dietary restrictions, options are available, and the diversity of the menu means there's likely a choice for everyone.

### Customer Experience & Service

While the culinary offerings at *Fat Fish* have largely drawn praise, the service aspect has been met with mixed reviews. Some guests have noted a need for enhanced training among waitstaff, mentioning instances of inconsistent service that detracted from their overall experience. However, those who have had attentive servers report friendly and efficient service, urging that your experience may vary depending on the day. The restaurant’s spacious parking also makes it convenient for patrons who arrive by car, ensuring a hassle-free experience right from the start.

### Popularity & Reviews

Social media buzz and customer sentiment lean positively in favor of *Fat Fish*. Many reviewers rave about the restaurant's great vibes and ideal settings for gatherings. Despite some critiques about service and pricing, the consensus is that the quality of food—particularly seafood dishes—makes it well worth the visit. Additionally, *Fat Fish* has garnered a reputation as a must-visit spot when in Calangute, prompting return trips from satisfied customers eager to try more of what the menu has to offer.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The vivid imagery shared by diners showcases not just the food but also the inviting environment of the restaurant. Photos depict vibrant dishes bursting with color and creativity—the seafood pizza presents as a drool-worthy spectacle—while images of the interior reveal a well-decorated space perfect for leisurely dining experiences.

In conclusion, *Fat Fish* encapsulates the essence of coastal dining in Arpora, serving up a delightful mix of fresh seafood in a casual yet charming setting. While slight improvements in service efficiency may enhance the experience, the restaurant's culinary creations have rightfully captured the hearts (and stomachs) of many who step through its doors.
